enumerations.name: SecurityEventContextDataSourceEnum
enumerations.note: This enumeration controls the elements used to creating the resulting qualified security event Tags: atp.Status=candidate Aggregated by SecurityEventAggregationFilter.contextDataSource

literals.name: useFirstContextData
literals.description:
Context data of first received security event shall be used for resulting qualified security event.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: useLastContextData
literals.description:
Context data of last received security event shall be used for resulting qualified security event.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

enumerations.name: SecurityEventReportingModeEnum
enumerations.note: This enumeration controls the reporting mode of a security event. Tags: atp.Status=candidate Aggregated by SecurityEventContextProps.defaultReportingMode

literals.name: brief
literals.description:
Only the main security event properties such as its ID are processed. Any additional context data (if
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

literals.name: briefBypassing
literals.description:
The reported security event without its context data (if existing) is processed further but the filter chain Filters is bypassed.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=3

literals.name: detailed
literals.description:
The main properties and the context data (if existing) of the reported security event are processed
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=2

literals.name: detailedBypassing
literals.description:
The reported security event including its context data (if existing) is processed further but the filter Filters chain is bypassed.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=4

literals.name: off
literals.description:
The reported security event is not further processed by the IdsM and therefore discarded.
